   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-BRISTOL (Bridgeport, Conn.) _ A look at the issues
raised by the civil antitrust trial brought by Bristol Technologies
against Microsoft in Bridgeport, Conn. By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   MORGAN-STANLEY (New York) _ Latest developments in the in-house
scandal at Morgan Stanley Dean Witter. By Joseph Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   MEDIA-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ What to make of so many mainline
media companies suddenly setting up separate Internet units:
Forbes, The New York Times, CNN? By Felicity Barringer.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   CULTUREFINDER (New York) _ Comcast Corp., a cable giant with
diverse holdings that include stakes in the television and online
versions of the QVC shopping channel and E Entertainment
Television, has added a more highbrow investment to its portfolio:
Culturefinder.com, a Web site that lists arts events and sells
tickets to exhibits, operas, symphonies, dance and theatrical
performances around the United States. By Jane L. Levere.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   DENVER-COMPETE-MEDIA (Denver) _ Fought with street vendors
hawking extra editions, two-year subscriptions going for a penny a
paper and advertising discounts that produce some of the world's
fattest newspapers, the flagship papers of two big newspaper
empires are locked in combat here. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
