</P>
<P>
   _If your road is unpaved, it is highly unlikely that Spokane
County will pave it without financing by the adjoining property
owners through a Road Improvement District.
 &UR; You want reliable, regular contact with the outside world? Dream
on:  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _Mail delivery may not be available to all areas of the county.
...
</P>
<P>
   _Newspaper delivery is not always available to rural areas. ...
</P>
<P>
   _Standard parcel and overnight package delivery can be a problem
for those who live in the country. ...
</P>
<P>
   _Telephone communications can be a problem, especially in the
mountainous areas of Spokane County. If you have a private line, it
may be difficult to obtain another line for fax or computer modem
uses. Even cellular phones may not work in all areas.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Our public utilities are second to some:  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _If you do not have access to a supply of treated domestic
water, you will have to locate an alternative supply. ...The cost
for drilling and pumping can be considerable. ...
</P>
<P>
   _Electric service may not be readily available in every area of
Spokane County. It is important to determine the proximity of
electrical power, as it can be very expensive to extend power lines
to remote areas. ...
</P>
<P>
   _Power outages can occur in outlying areas with more frequency
than in more developed areas, particularly if power lines are
