<P>
   THE HOLIDAY DUTY EDITORS ARE:
</P>
<P>
   IN ATLANTA: Tom Oder at (office) 404 526-5456 or (pager)
800-495-2461 or pagetom(at)coxnews.com
</P>
<P>
   IN WASHINGTON: Andy Glass at (home) 202 363-2389.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   GORE-WOMEN _ WASHINGTON _ Women have always strongly supported
Al Gore in his quest for office, and a new group of female
supporters is being formed Tuesday with the backing of first lady
Hillary Rodham Clinton. But will Gore's backing of the Kosovo war
erode that support? (Shepard, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   SHOOT-HEARING _ ATLANTA _ A judge will decide today whether T.J.
Solomon should be tried as an adult fir shooting six of his
Heritage High School Classmates. The community is divided on the
issue. Some say let the juvenile justice system work; let Solomon
be rehabilitated. Others say he should be tried as an adult because
he committed adult crimes. (Stanford, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   BELLSOUTH-PAGERS _ ATLANTA - BellSouth's interactive pagers,
which are sold nationwide, will be sold by the wireless folks in
the Southeast. The idea is to give the wireless phone unit, which
has been faulted for being regional in competition with big
national players, another weapon in the war against Sprint and
AT&AMP;T. (Kannell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (f) Financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   MEDIA0NE-DIGITALTV _ ATLANTA _ MediaOne will begin offering
digital television to a small group of its customers in the Atlanta
area for the first time beginning June 1. The service, to be called
MediaOne Digital NexTV, will be available to about a third of
MediaOne's 95,000 subscribers in suburban west Cobb County. It will
offer 222 channels of music, premium movie services and
pay-for-view programming. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (f) Financial categories.
</P>
