<HEADLINE>
`WINCHELL' TRACES THE LIFE OF A COMPLICATED FIGURE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Winchell'' _ Stanley Tucci stars as the powerful
columnist/commentator who symbolized the growing power of the
media. A combination of gossip monger and power broker, Winchell
was a complicated figure brought to uncomfortable life in this
biography, which originally aired on HBO.
</P>
<P>
   ``Berenstain Bears'' (three new episodes) _ The popular animated
bears, a big hit on home video, add three more stories to their
oeuvre. Perfect for the preschool set.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dolphins: The Wild Side'' _ National Geographic continues its
remarkable documentary tradition with the stunningly filmed account
of dolphins using teamwork and sonar to trap their prey. No Flipper
here. These mammals are tough.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: Sales of the DVD versions of ``A Bug's Life'' and
``Antz'' have led family titles on DVD to almost twice last year's
children's figures. Last year, non-action titles (family, comedy,
romance) made up 13 percent of the market, according to recent data
compiled by industry observers, the DVD Video Group and VideoScan.
So far this year, the non-action genres make up 25 percent of the
market; when Disney begins releasing its classic animation on DVD
in the near future, that figure should climb. Eleven of the 25
top-selling titles this year fall in the categories of family,
romance, or comedy. (The figures are based on sales data collected
by VideoScan from retail locations nationwide, including Best Buy,
Blockbuster, Circuit City, Musicland, Tower Records, and more, but
do not include small specialty stores and mass merchants such as
Wal-Mart and Kmart.) &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: June 8: ``From the Earth to the Moon,''
``Treehouse Hostage,'' ``Psycho'' (remake), ``Gods and Monsters,''
``Before Stonewall,'' ``After Stonewall,'' ``Last Rites.'' June 15:
``Little Voice,'' ``The World Within,'' ``Enemy of the State,''
``The Faculty,'' ``Facade,'' ``The Patriot.'' June 22: ``Waking Ned
Devine,'' ``Patch Adams,'' ``A Simple Plan,'' ``Rushmore,''
``Wishful Thinking,'' ``Sweethearts,'' ``The Life of Birds,''
``Storm of the Century.'' June 29: ``The Thin Red Line,'' ``Varsity
Blues,'' ``Lansky.'' July 6: ``The King and I'' (animated), ``The
Red and the White.'' July 13: ``Life Is Beautiful,'' ``A Civil
Action,'' ``She's All That.'' July 20: ``Down in the Delta,''
``Telling You,'' ``Mercenary 2: Thick and Thin.''
</P>
</TEXT>
