<SLUG> BC-ANDERSON-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TALENTED TATTLER TERRIBLY GOOD AT WHAT HE DOES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MONICA FRAZIER ANDERSON 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Would someone from Tattler's Anonymous please call and let me
know the time and place of your next meeting? I need to enroll my
baby boy in your 14-step program. (I know it usually only takes 12
steps, but he's got it bad.)
</P>
<P>
   He doesn't know the meaning of the word ``closemouthed.''
</P>
<P>
   He doesn't know the meaning of the word ``discretion.''
</P>
<P>
   He doesn't know the meaning of ``privileged information.''
</P>
<P>
   I know, he doesn't know the meaning of a lot of words because
he's just a kid, but things are getting out of hand. I truly wish
that he'd stop taking his self-appointed role as the thorn in his
big brother's side quite so seriously.
</P>
<P>
   I have to say, my youngest man has a talent for telling.
</P>
<P>
   Before he learned his ABCs, he had memorized my work number, my
cell phone number, my pager number and my fax number. He could
track me down better than a Dixie bloodhound.
</P>
<P>
   As time passed, the novelty of his Junior Central Intelligence
Agency wore off, and I had to tell him to stop calling me every
time his brother forgot to cover his mouth when he coughed. That's
when he started sending faxes to my office.
</P>
<P>
   The latest one was typical _ a report on the subversive activity
going on in my own home at that very moment:
</P>
<P>
   To: Monica Anderson
</P>
<P>
   From: Jacob Anderson
</P>
<P>
   No. of Pages: 1 (including cover)
</P>
<P>
   Message: My brother has been using the same face towel for three
weeks. I think that is why he has those little bumps on his nose
and forehead. Please call home and punish him. Maybe you should
give his new basketball to me.
</P>
<P>
   Yours very truly,
</P>
<P>
   The Good Son
</P>
<P>
   I hate to cut him off from this completely for fear that one day
he'll have some really juicy information on his brother and decide
not to give it up. But it occurs to me that there is a downside to
this. If he keeps this up and his interest starts to spread, soon
my husband will know what really happened to that box of delicious,
hot Krispy Kreme doughnuts.
</P>
<P>
   Yes, I guess that settles it.
</P>
<P>
   You TA folks? Please give me a call. If you need my phone
number, just check with my son.
</P>
<P>
   He'll tell you anything you want to know.
</P>
<P>
   (Monica Frazier Anderson is an Arlington, Texas, wife, mother
and dentist. Write in care of the ``Arlington Star-Telegram'' at
1111 W. Abram St., Arlington, TX 76013. Visit the Star-Telegram's
online services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
