<HEADLINE>
DENIM, RIGHT DOWN TO THE TOES 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Denim has made such a strong comeback that it is
being used for many things other than jeans. There are dresses,
shorts, shoes and bags in different shades of blue.
</P>
<P>
   A cap-sleeve dress by Claudie Pierlot is $125 at Bergdorf
Goodman, and a shift with spaghetti straps by Mimi Turner is $185
at Barneys New York. Barneys also has knee-length shorts by Grab &AMP;
Mac, $150, and Daryl K, $144; a zip-front vest by Mimi Turner,
$160, and square-toed flat slippers in blue or black by Martin
Margiela, $255.
</P>
<P>
   The Kate Spade store, 454 Broome St., at Mercer Street, has four
bags in dark denim: a bucket with a leather handle, a
short-strapped shoulder bag and two handbags. They range from $215
to $260.
</P>
<P>
   Neiman Marcus has an embroidered small flat tote by Patch NYC,
$198; a hobo in light blue by Moschino, $340; a dark blue baguette
bag with orange stitching, $375, and a U-shaped shoulder bag by
Fendi, $425.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
