   KOSOVO-CLINTON (Washington) _ Speaking on the eve of an
important meeting of NATO military leaders in Belgium, where
officials are expected to finalize planning for the Yugoslav
peacekeeping force, President Clinton says that the peacekeeping
force now being assembled will be predominantly European and that
European nations will pay most of the costs of reconstructiong
