services. BellSouth believes they will sometimes appeal to
different users, while some users will carry both.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are some things I can deal with without dialing a
phone,'' Madara said. ``Cell phones ringing in a meeting can be
very distracting, but (with an interactive pager) I can type back a
message and nobody in the room even knows I am doing it.''
</P>
<P>
   The interactive pager has also been known to let two people in a
meeting send each other messages.
</P>
<P>
   Michael E. Kanell writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
