   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CLINTON (Washington) _ On the eve of a key NATO decision
on how to assemble a large peacekeeping force for Yugoslavia,
President Clinton says that Europeans will contribute most of the
force and would pay most of the cost of rebuilding Yugoslavia. By
John N. Broder. (We plan to move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i''
news file.) 1,200 words.
</P>
