MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - The letter from the woman began, ``Two
and one-half years ago, my formally considerate, loving, obedient
15-year-old son walked in the door and informed me that he didn't
have to do anything I said anymore.'' She was determined to prove
him wrong. But, it turns out the kid was right. By E.J. MONTINI
