 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MEDIA-TALK-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, May 30,
about the scaling back of coverage of refugees from Kosovo,
referred incorrectly to the current assignments in Macedonia and
Albania by The New York Times and by The Washington Post. Neither
paper has cut back its coverage. (One of four Times correspondents
assigned there left temporarily, to complete a report about the
purging of Kosovar Albanians by Serbian forces. The Post plans to
keep at least four correspondents there.)
</P>
